    <article>
      <h2>General tips</h2>
      <p><strong>Concatenate your stylesheets and javascripts</strong></p>
      <p>Got a bunch of stylesheets? Put them all together to make them extra speedy. This means fewer HTTP requests, which means less overhead for your users, and faster-loading pages.</p>

      <div class="example">
        <code class="before">
          <pre>
&lt;link href="normalize.css" />
&lt;link href="style.css" />
&lt;link href="pages.css" />
&lt;link href="buttons.css" /></pre>
        </code>
        <code class="after">
          <pre>
&lt;link href="public.css" /></pre>
        </code>
      </div>

      <p class="info">If you're using <a href="http://hammerformac.com">Hammer for Mac</a>, remember to build with "Optimized" mode enabled.</p>
    </article>
      
